The paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the computer science sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the incorporation of both mechanistic and phenomenological approaches, which is a topic in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning in spatial cognition, which is a topic in the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
